## ğŸ“¬ 5. The HTTP Request Structure

```
GET /index.html HTTP/1.1
Host: example.com
User-Agent: Chrome/120.0
Accept: text/html
```

### ğŸ§± Components

| Part        | Description                              |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| **Method**  | What action you want (GET, POST, PUT...) |
| **Path**    | The resource or route youâ€™re requesting  |
| **Headers** | Extra information (auth, type, language) |
| **Body**    | Data you send (only for POST/PUT)        |

---

## ğŸ“¦ 6. The HTTP Response Structure

```
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/html
Content-Length: 345

<html> ... </html>
```

| Part            | Description                           |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| **Status Line** | Protocol + Status code (e.g. 200 OK)  |
| **Headers**     | Metadata like content type or cookies |
| **Body**        | Actual data (HTML, JSON, image, etc.) |

---

## ğŸ“Š 7. Common HTTP Status Codes

| Code                             | Meaning       | Description                     |
| -------------------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------------- |
| âœ… **200 OK**                     | Success       | Request completed successfully  |
| ğŸ•µï¸ **301 Moved Permanently**    | Redirect      | Resource moved to a new URL     |
| âš ï¸ **400 Bad Request**           | Client Error  | Wrong syntax or invalid request |
| ğŸ”’ **401 Unauthorized**          | Auth Error    | Missing or invalid credentials  |
| ğŸš« **403 Forbidden**             | Access Denied | You donâ€™t have permission       |
| âŒ **404 Not Found**              | Not Found     | Resource doesnâ€™t exist          |
| ğŸ’£ **500 Internal Server Error** | Server Error  | Something went wrong on server  |

